  <discussion>B. Mathew (1989b) noted that the cultivated Lewisia columbiana ‘Rosea’ is this
        variety. B. L. Davidson (2000) noted that the United States populations have pink to magenta
        petals, whereas the British Columbia populations have white to pale pink petals
        characteristic of the other varieties. Mathew questioned the assignment of the British
        Columbia plants to this variety.</discussion>
